*******************************************************************************
       Name: Sacred Ward
       Kind: Spell
     Target: TAR_IGNORE (room/group)
   Position: POS_STANDING
   Min Mana: 80
 Wait Beats: 24
 Can Learn: FALSE
Noun Damage: None
   Wear-Off: The sacred ward's warmth fades.
Acquisition:
   - Templar: level 5
Description:
   Sacred Ward calls forth holy power to bless the ground, applying a
   heal-over-time (HOT) effect to all grouped allies in the room. This
   reflects the Templar's role as a threshold guardian who "consecrates
   spaces" -- securing and sanctifying contested locations.

   Duration: 6 + (Templar level / 4) rounds
   HOT modifier: Templar level * 3 + Paladin level + Priest level
   Mana cost: 80

   Distinct from the Cleric's "consecrate" spell (which grants hitroll/AC
   to group and damages evil NPCs). Sacred Ward focuses on sustained
   healing throughput for the group rather than offensive holy damage.
*******************************************************************************
